TWO people were killed in separate accidents on the M7 West Bound, Wakesleigh Road, in Durban this weekend.  In Sunday’s accident Advanced Life Support (ALS) paramedics spokesperson Rowan Scandroglio confirmed one person had been killed in a horrific accident on the M7 west bound at Wakesleigh Road just after noon.  “ALS Paramedics Medical Services arrived on the scene to find total carnage. A light motor vehicle had somehow lost control before a collision with the back of a truck at the intersection. One person, a male believed to be in his forties, sustained fatal injuries and there was nothing more paramedics could do for him and he was declared deceased on the scene.”   Scandroglio added the events leading up to the accident were unknown and police were on the scene and will be investigating further. In a separate crash,  ALS paramedics spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said one person died in a serious accident on the M7 West bound at Wakesleigh Road just after 2am on Saturday morning.  “A truck and a light delivery vehicle collided at the intersection. The driver of the light delivery vehicle, a male in his forties, was found to have sustained fatal injuries and there was nothing paramedics could do for him and he was declared deceased on the scene. The driver of the truck sustained no injuries.” Jamieson added that police would be investigating further.  “At this stage the events leading up to the incident are unknown, however SAPS were on the scene and will be investigating further.”    THE MERCURY